SECURITY ASSESSMENT NOTE:
Reusing the same XOR key across multiple ciphertexts enables
known-plaintext attacks and crib-dragging analysis. An attacker
who knows any part of any plaintext message can derive the key
and decrypt all other messages encrypted with the same key.

Immediate key rotation is strongly recommended.

